  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 1, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into thin chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1695043653259-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1695043653259-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1695043653259-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1695043653259-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1695043653259-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine 1/4 of your <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>(save the rest for later!) in a bowl with your <strong>curry powder</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>tandoori</strong> <strong>marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chicken breast portions</strong> to the <strong>tandoori marinade </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>marinated chicken</strong></p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized thighs? Butterfly the thicker ones by cutting them in half like a burger bun (but don’t cut the whole way through!) then open them up</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>marinated chicken </strong>to one side of a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 17-18 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and starting to char – this is your <strong>tandoori chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, grate the <strong>cucumber</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated cucumber</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>remaining natural yoghurt</strong>, <strong>mint sauce</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and mix it all together – this is your <strong>cucumber raita</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Once the chicken is nearly cooked, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>sliced brioche bun[s]</strong> to the other side of the tray[s]</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 3-4 min or until the brioche is warmed through and toasted</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To assemble, spread a dollop of <strong>cucumber raita</strong> on the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>brioche base</strong>, then fill with the <strong>tandoori chicken</strong>, more <strong>cucumber raita </strong>and <strong>mango chutney </strong>– this is your <strong>tandoori chicken burger</strong></p><p>Serve the<strong> tandoori chicken burger </strong>with the <strong>chips </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
